You are helping create a 3–4 slide executive-level presentation for a completed project.

Context:

The presentation will be delivered by a senior manager (T) to CEO and C-level executives.
The audience is non-technical or semi-technical. They care about business impact, risk, and strategic value, not implementation details.
The project is already completed. This is not a proposal - it is a concise executive readout.
The goal is to clearly explain why the initiative mattered, what was done, and what value it created for the organization.

Instructions:

Use a clear storytelling structure inspired by SCQA, but do NOT explicitly label slides as SCQA.
Instead, structure the deck as:
Challenge (Situation + Complication)
Response (What was done)
Impact (Business value)
(Optional) Future / What this enables next

Output requirements:

Create a 4-slide plan with:
Slide title
1-line subtitle (executive-friendly, not technical)
3–5 bullet points per slide
Keep language concise, executive-level, and business-focused.
Avoid technical jargon unless it directly supports business value (risk reduction, scalability, cost, compliance).
Focus on:
Why this mattered to the business
What problem or risk was addressed
What changed as a result
Why leadership should care now
